This should be fixed. The codes running here shouldn't make assumption on the number of log files. Reading from https://github.com/logrotate/logrotate/issues/224, seems like logrotate doesn't pad zip files. If that's the case, we should implement codes to compare numeric strings without padding, which should be straightforward: 

```
// No leading zeros
[](const std::string& suffix1, const std::string& suffix2) -> bool {
  return std::forward_as_tuple(suffix1.size(), suffix1) > std::forward_as_tuple(suffix2.size(), suffix2);
}; 
```
